content:
Prepare for Restrictions on Salesforce Cookie Use

To test custom functionality and code that uses a Salesforce session cookie before browsers fully block third-party cookies, enable the My Domain setting, Require first-party use of Salesforce cookies. For example, to load your authenticated Visualforce page in an iframe on a third-party website, the process uses a Salesforce session cookie.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic in Group, Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions.

Why: Major web browsers block third-party cookies by default. Users can configure some browsers to allow these cookies, but browser developers intend to stop offering that option.

How: To prevent third-party use of Salesforce cookies, from Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter My Domain, and then select My Domain. In the Routing and Policies section, click Edit. Enable Require first-party use of Salesforce cookies, and save your changes.

IMPORTANT This setting only affects Salesforce cookies. To test calls from Salesforce that use a third-party cookie, including third-party applications embedded in Salesforce, disable third-party cookies in your browser.

SEE ALSO
Salesforce Help: Test the Impact of Blocked Salesforce Session Cookies
title: Prepare for Salesforce Cookie Restrictions
